    "chunk_id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2009_Solutions_2009s_page_001_22",
    "text": "Remark. More generally, no rational number of the form m/n, where m,n are relatively prime and neither of Em is a quadratic residue mod n, need be in S. If x = p/q is in lowest terms and 1/xx - 1)) = m/n +k for some integer k, then p(p -q) is relatively prime to 47; 97/(p(p -9)) = (m + kn) /n then implies that m + kn = q and so ‡m must be a quadratic residue mod n.",
